Set the MAVEN_HOME environment variable to the installation directory of Maven 3.6.3.
Add the MAVEN_HOME/bin directory to your PATH


Create a Toolchains File
Create a file named toolchains.xml in the .m2 directory (usually located in your home directory, e.g., ~/.m2/toolchains.xml).
Add the following configuration to specify Maven 3.6.3
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF8"?>
<toolchains>
  <toolchain>
    <type>maven</type>
    <provides>
      <version>3.6.3</version>
    </provides>
    <configuration>
      <home>/path/to/your/maven-3.6.3</home>
    </configuration>
  </toolchain>
</toolchains>


Ensure that your settings.xml file (located in the .m2 directory) includes the following configuration to enable toolchains:
<settings>
  ...
  <toolchains>
    <toolchain>
      <type>maven</type>
      <provides>
        <version>3.6.3</version>
      </provides>
    </toolchain>
  </toolchains>
  ...
</settings>
